1
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:30,754
<i>Remembering, out of the black silence...</i>

2
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:33,958
<i>you were born in pain.</i>

3
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:40,635
<i>Easy. Easy does it, little mother.</i>

4
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:43,766
<i>We've never lost a father.</i>

5
00:00:46,746 --> 00:00:49,738
<i>Your job is done, little mother.</i>

6
00:00:53,753 --> 00:00:56,916
<i>You were born with hate and anger built in.</i>

7
00:00:57,023 --> 00:01:00,186
<i>Took a slap on the backside</i>
<i>to blast out the scream...</i>

8
00:01:00,293 --> 00:01:02,921
<i>and then you knew you were alive.</i>

9
00:01:03,029 --> 00:01:05,520
<i>Eight pounds, five ounces.</i>

10
00:01:05,632 --> 00:01:08,123
<i>Baby boy Frankie Bono.</i>

11
00:01:08,234 --> 00:01:10,202
<i>Father doing well.</i>

12
00:01:14,607 --> 00:01:17,542
<i>Later you learned to</i>
<i>hold back the scream...</i>

13
00:01:17,644 --> 00:01:20,135
<i>and let out the hate and anger</i>
<i>another way.</i>

14
00:01:26,953 --> 00:01:30,889
<i>You come into Manhattan by dark,</i>
<i>whatever time of day it is...</i>

15
00:01:30,990 --> 00:01:34,289
<i>through tunnels,</i>
<i>like sewers hidden under the city.</i>

16
00:01:34,394 --> 00:01:38,888
<i>But you don't mind that.</i>
<i>It's always that way, whatever city it is.</i>

17
00:02:01,821 --> 00:02:04,813
<i>You're alone.</i>
<i>But you don't mind that.</i>

18
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:07,484
<i>You're a loner.</i>
<i>That's the way it should be.</i>

19
00:02:07,594 --> 00:02:09,528
<i>You've always been alone.</i>

20
00:02:09,629 --> 00:02:11,859
<i>By now it's your trademark.</i>

21
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,399
<i>You like it that way.</i>

22
00:02:22,542 --> 00:02:27,673
<i># Silent night #</i>

23
00:02:28,848 --> 00:02:32,841
<i>The railroad company makes sure you don't</i>
<i>forget you're coming to town on Christmas.</i>

24
00:02:32,952 --> 00:02:34,886
<i>It gives you the creeps.</i>

25
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:39,823
<i>But that's all right.</i>
<i>Everyone on the goodwill kick,</i>
<i>maybe they'll leave you alone.</i>

26
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:09,253
<i>You hate cities,</i>
<i>especially at Christmas.</i>

27
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,255
<i>But that's all right too.</i>

28
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:13,825
<i>When the Better Business Bureau</i>
<i>rings the Christmas bell...</i>

29
00:03:13,927 --> 00:03:16,555
<i>the suckers forget</i>
<i>there's such a business as murder...</i>

30
00:03:16,663 --> 00:03:19,791
<i>and businessmen</i>
<i>who make it their exclusive line.</i>

31
00:03:19,899 --> 00:03:23,562
<i>Like you.</i>
<i>Baby boy Frankie Bono.</i>

32
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:25,638
<i>Out of Cleveland.</i>

33
00:03:42,088 --> 00:03:44,056
Nice view we have here.

34
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,720
Thank you, mister.
Merry Christmas.

35
00:03:51,831 --> 00:03:53,958
<i>Registered as Fred Moore of Albany.</i>

36
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:57,503
<i>In town for a week or less,</i>
<i>on business.</i>

37
00:03:57,604 --> 00:04:00,767
By the way, mister, if you need anything,
just ask for George.

38
00:04:00,873 --> 00:04:02,841
Okay.

39
00:04:07,847 --> 00:04:11,010
<i>At noon, you make contact.</i>

40
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:13,416
<i>The wind is cold as you
approach the ferry...</i>

41
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:16,010
<i>but the palms of your hands</i>
<i>start to sweat.</i>

42
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:23,452
<i>This is the first bad moment.</i>

43
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:26,532
<i>There's always a few on every job</i>
<i>when you're not alone.</i>

44
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,658
<i>You can depend on yourself,</i>
<i>no one else.</i>

45
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:31,293
<i>You've learned the hard way.</i>

46
00:04:31,404 --> 00:04:33,702
<i>They all hate the gun they hire.</i>

47
00:04:33,806 --> 00:04:38,266
<i>When people look at you,</i>
<i>baby boy Frankie Bono, they see death</i>--

48
00:04:38,378 --> 00:04:40,278
<i>death across the counter.</i>

49
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,348
<i>Remembering.</i>

50
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:59,192
<i>Watch it, Frankie.</i>
<i>You almost missed him.</i>

51
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:02,894
<i>You'll know him by the hate in his eye</i>
<i>when he asks for a light.</i>

52
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:05,938
You got a match, bud?

53
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,754
Ever been in Ohio?

54
00:05:22,855 --> 00:05:24,720
Yeah. Cleveland.

55
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:27,816
I got a friend that practices in Cleveland.

56
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:32,823
- <i>You know him?</i>
- Yeah, I know Fat Nick.

57
00:05:32,932 --> 00:05:34,832
You got my passport?

58
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:42,269
Half the dough is in the envelope. You get
the other half when the job is finished.

59
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:45,469
- How do I get in touch?
- <i>There's a number in the envelope.</i>

60
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:49,014
<i>Call after you make the hit. I'll let you know</i>
<i>where to meet me for the payoff.</i>

61
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,015
Okay.

62
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:53,085
Uh, one more thing.

63
00:05:55,355 --> 00:06:00,122
If you get spotted before the hit,
the contract's off. You understand me?

64
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:04,094
Yeah, I understand ya.

65
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,796
<i>Now you're alone again.</i>

66
00:06:12,905 --> 00:06:17,069
<i>You relax. Your hands are cold now,</i>
<i>even with gloves on.</i>

67
00:06:17,176 --> 00:06:20,304
<i>On your own again.</i>
<i>Nothing to worry about.</i>

68
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:33,317
<i>The target's name is Troiano.</i>
<i>You know the type.</i>

69
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:36,554
<i>Second-string syndicate boss</i>
<i>with too much ambition...</i>

70
00:06:36,662 --> 00:06:40,393
<i>and a mustache</i>
<i>to hide the fact he has lips like a woman...</i>

71
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,934
<i>the kind of face you hate.</i>

72
00:06:54,614 --> 00:06:56,673
<i>Nice little home.</i>

73
00:06:56,783 --> 00:06:58,808
<i>Quiet little community.</i>

74
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:01,148
<i>An hour out in the suburbs.</i>

75
00:07:02,388 --> 00:07:04,982
<i>Every morning he's picked up</i>
<i>by two bodyguards.</i>

76
00:07:06,392 --> 00:07:08,292
<i>Hood written all over them.</i>

77
00:07:08,394 --> 00:07:11,386
<i>But when the neighbors read</i>
<i>the headlines, "Mobster Killed"...</i>

78
00:07:11,497 --> 00:07:16,298
<i>they'll say, "But Mr. Troiano seemed like</i>
<i>such a respectable man.</i>

79
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:20,031
<i>He went to work every morning,</i>
<i>9:30 on the dot."</i>

80
00:07:28,748 --> 00:07:32,013
<i>You already know one thing:</i>
<i>You can't make the kill at his house.</i>

81
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:34,018
<i>Too easily spotted.</i>

82
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,088
<i>Twenty-four hour streetlamps.</i>

83
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:43,085
<i>It's a laugh.</i>

84
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:46,632
<i>You could afford a house like that,</i>
<i>if you wanted it.</i>

85
00:07:46,732 --> 00:07:48,962
<i>You're in the upper</i>
<i>five percent income bracket.</i>

86
00:07:49,068 --> 00:07:52,060
<i>Killing pays well,</i>
<i>for a reason.</i>

87
00:07:52,171 --> 00:07:56,540
<i>You have the experience and the know-how.</i>
<i>You're proud of your reputation.</i>

88
00:07:56,642 --> 00:07:59,110
<i>Expert and thorough.</i>

89
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:01,612
<i>You don't have to know a man</i>
<i>to live with him.</i>

90
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:04,945
<i>But you have to know a man</i>
<i>like a brother to kill him.</i>

91
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:25,267
<i>Watch it.</i>

92
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:27,271
<i>Bodyguards slowing down.</i>

93
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:29,307
<i>Could be they're watching for a tail.</i>

94
00:08:29,408 --> 00:08:31,308
<i>Pass them.</i>

95
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:34,504
<i>Don't ever take chances.</i>
<i>You're not a gambler.</i>

96
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,419
<i>Now you know the pattern</i>
<i>the job will take:</i>

97
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,459
<i>a waiting job.</i>

98
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:50,028
<i>Waiting to find where Troiano goes</i>
<i>to be alone.</i>

99
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:52,063
<i>And you know another thing.</i>

100
00:08:52,164 --> 00:08:54,064
<i>It'll have to be quick and silent...</i>

101
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:56,259
<i>while he's away from his bodyguards.</i>

102
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:59,702
<i>It'll be a job for a gun.</i>
<i>That means another bad moment.</i>

103
00:08:59,805 --> 00:09:01,705
<i>Another contact.</i>

104
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:03,900
<i>Your hands sweat a little</i>
<i>on the wheel...</i>

105
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:08,071
<i>remembering another Christmas</i>
<i>running from the cops.</i>

106
00:09:16,989 --> 00:09:20,447
<i>Watch it, Frankie.</i>
<i>Danger signal. Your mind's wandering.</i>

107
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,891
<i>But you know why.</i>

108
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:26,328
<i>You have to do business with Ralphie,</i>
<i>and he turns your stomach.</i>

109
00:09:48,955 --> 00:09:51,423
Oh, yeah.

110
00:09:51,524 --> 00:09:53,424
Uh, Frankie, huh?

111
00:09:53,526 --> 00:09:55,426
- Uh --
- Bono.

112
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:57,894
Bono. Hey, yeah. Come on in.

113
00:09:57,997 --> 00:09:59,965
Geez. It's good to see ya.

114
00:10:02,668 --> 00:10:05,660
You really surprised me.
I didn't expect nobody.

115
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,966
Kids been knocking on the door all day.

116
00:10:08,074 --> 00:10:10,008
Trying to bother me, you know.

117
00:10:18,684 --> 00:10:23,587
<i>Place is kind of a mess. You have to excuse</i>
<i>me. I didn't expect no company or nothing.</i>

118
00:10:25,992 --> 00:10:29,428
I just had my lunch here. Hey.

119
00:10:31,597 --> 00:10:34,327
So how you been?
You makin' a dollar?

120
00:10:34,433 --> 00:10:36,333
- Doin' all right.
- Yeah?

121
00:10:36,435 --> 00:10:39,268
Yeah. Yeah, you always did all right.

122
00:10:39,372 --> 00:10:42,000
- Sit down, Frank.
- <i>I'm in a hurry, Ralph.</i>

123
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:45,874
Ah. Uh, you got one of them for me?

124
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:52,613
I, uh --

125
00:10:55,955 --> 00:10:57,923
I heard you did a little time, huh?

126
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:01,959
Still in business, Ralphie.

127
00:11:02,061 --> 00:11:04,029
What can I --
What can I do for you?

128
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:07,031
- I need a piece.
- That's no problem.

129
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,101
Thirty-eight with a silencer.

130
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:12,627
Oh.

131
00:11:12,738 --> 00:11:15,263
A silencer, huh?

132
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,977
That, uh --

133
00:11:20,046 --> 00:11:24,278
That may, uh, be a little problem.

134
00:11:24,383 --> 00:11:26,351
You know, I, uh --

135
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:30,219
I gotta worry about a machinist.

136
00:11:30,322 --> 00:11:32,290
But, uh...

137
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:37,189
we'll work something out.

138
00:11:37,296 --> 00:11:39,230
But it'll cost ya.

139
00:11:43,903 --> 00:11:47,100
Hey, Nancy.
How you doing, huh?

140
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:49,106
Coo, coo, coo.

141
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:52,439
Look how she knows me, huh?
How you doing, sweetie?

142
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:55,343
Coo, coo, coo, coo, coo, coo.

143
00:11:55,448 --> 00:11:58,042
Bop, bop, bop, bop, bop.

144
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:02,143
- Bop, bop, bop, bop, bop.
- How much?

145
00:12:02,254 --> 00:12:04,848
She hasn't eaten all day.
Let me get her something.

146
00:12:07,526 --> 00:12:10,256
Here you go.
Here you go, sweetie.

147
00:12:10,362 --> 00:12:13,923
Hey. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Ah!

148
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:17,366
Come on.
Yeah. You like that, don't you?

149
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:20,268
You like that.

150
00:12:20,372 --> 00:12:22,533
$500, Frank.

151
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,143
Coo, coo, coo, coo.

152
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:31,706
- I'll give you two. - Oh, I'd like
to help you out, Frank, but two?

153
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:33,785
Ah.

154
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:40,056
Come on. Come on.
Here you go.

155
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:43,193
There's another one.

156
00:12:43,295 --> 00:12:45,957
I'll tell you what I'll do, Frank.

157
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:48,829
$400. But that's rock bottom.

158
00:12:51,804 --> 00:12:54,568
Three.

159
00:12:54,673 --> 00:12:58,006
A yard and a half now,
and the rest when I get the piece.

160
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,738
Aw, Frank, make it another 50.
Come on.

161
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:03,781
What does it mean to you?
I gotta make something on the deal.

162
00:13:03,883 --> 00:13:07,046
Just another 50.
Come on, Frank. Please.

163
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:13,021
All right. I'll give you the other 50.
But that's it.

164
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,753
- Do you understand?
- Sure. Sure, Frank.

165
00:13:15,861 --> 00:13:17,761
When I make a deal, it's a deal.

166
00:13:17,863 --> 00:13:19,763
Now we'll have a drink, huh?

167
00:13:19,865 --> 00:13:22,095
I'm in a hurry, Ralph.
Where do I pick it up?

168
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:24,897
Aw, just one for the new year, Frank.

169
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:30,265
Hey.

170
00:13:30,376 --> 00:13:34,676
Whatever happened to that, uh --
that girl you used to go with, the redhead?

171
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:36,748
What was her name?

172
00:13:38,717 --> 00:13:41,345
Sally. Yeah.
Hey, Frank.

173
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:43,353
She, uh --

174
00:13:43,455 --> 00:13:45,389
She liked me, didn't she?

175
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:47,425
Yeah. She liked you.

176
00:13:47,526 --> 00:13:50,552
Yeah. Here's to, uh --

177
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:52,756
Here's to Sally.

178
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:55,163
Ralph, where do I get the goods?

179
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:57,531
Oh, yeah. Over on the East Side.

180
00:13:57,636 --> 00:14:00,969
There's a barge called the <i>Katherine L.</i>
Pier 21.

181
00:14:01,073 --> 00:14:04,839
Ask to speak to Joe Boniface.
Tell him Vinny Sintera sent you.

182
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:07,378
Tell him you're from Cleveland.
He'll deliver the goods.

183
00:14:08,414 --> 00:14:11,349
- Where is that near?
- Between 23rd and 24th Street.

184
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:16,579
- And I want this quick.
- Oh, yeah. Anytime after tomorrow, Frank.

185
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:21,149
- All right.
- Hey. Wh-What's your rush, Frank?

186
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:25,629
- Gotta run, Ralphie.
- I thought we could talk over old times.

187
00:14:35,674 --> 00:14:37,608
Hey.

188
00:14:38,644 --> 00:14:40,544
Look here, huh?

189
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:43,342
Look what big Ralph got for Christmas.
Isn't that nice?

190
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:46,509
Yeah. Isn't that nice?

191
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:27,650
<i>Now you're alone again,
in another rented car.</i>

192
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,957
<i>You pick up the target</i>
<i>where you left off yesterday...</i>

193
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:33,031
<i>right on schedule.</i>

194
00:15:36,802 --> 00:15:41,398
<i>Today the breaks are with you,</i>
<i>and you stay with him while</i>
<i>he makes his morning rounds.</i>

195
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:44,135
<i>The streets of Harlem are busy enough.</i>
<i>No one notices you.</i>

196
00:15:44,243 --> 00:15:46,973
<i>You catch a danger signal.</i>

197
00:15:47,079 --> 00:15:50,879
<i>Your hands are sweating, but that's</i>
<i>all right, because you know what it is:</i>

198
00:15:50,983 --> 00:15:52,883
<i>the hate of Harlem.</i>

199
00:15:52,985 --> 00:15:55,545
<i>You hate them, and they hate you.</i>

200
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:58,418
<i>Like another Harlem</i>
<i>where you grew up.</i>

201
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:12,504
<i>Watch it, Frankie.</i>
<i>Save your hate for Troiano.</i>

202
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:15,869
<i>He runs the girls and the dope</i>
<i>and the books and the numbers.</i>

203
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,500
<i>There's a guy you could
really learn to hate.</i>

204
00:16:18,610 --> 00:16:22,171
<i>You will, before the time comes.</i>
<i>You always do.</i>

205
00:16:22,281 --> 00:16:25,944
<i>Somehow you always hate the targets</i>
<i>before you hit 'em.</i>

206
00:16:37,396 --> 00:16:42,993
<i>The sisters at the orphanage used to say,</i>
<i>"God moves in mysterious ways."</i>

207
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:48,936
<i>Sometimes you wonder if he moved you in</i>
<i>to rid the world of men like Troiano.</i>

208
00:16:57,282 --> 00:17:00,683
<i>He thinks he looks like a gentleman</i>
<i>if his shoes are shined.</i>

209
00:17:00,786 --> 00:17:03,254
<i>You could kill him</i>
<i>right now with pleasure.</i>

210
00:17:43,028 --> 00:17:44,962
<i>Knock it off for today.</i>

211
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,259
<i>Pick him up tomorrow</i>
<i>when he leaves the restaurant.</i>

212
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:01,676
<i>Time to kill. Twenty-four hours</i>
<i>to stay faceless in the crowd.</i>

213
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:04,146
<i>Get yourself lost in the city.</i>

214
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:07,184
<i>Lose yourself in the Christmas spirit</i>
<i>with the rest of the suckers.</i>

215
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:12,690
Ho, ho, ho, ho!
Hello! Hello, little boys and girls.

